headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 10 of Philadelphia's 13 overtime points Sunday and finished with a season-high 45 as the 76ers beat the Indiana Pacers 118-114 for their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Maxey scores 10 in OT, finishes with 45 points as 76ers beat Pacers 118-114

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 28 points to lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 125-103 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Sunday for their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jerami Grant scores 28 and Blazers beat Pelicans 125-103 for first win of the season

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 35 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Atlanta Hawks 128-104 on Sunday night in a matchup of teams that had won their first two games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander's 35 points help Thunder pull away for 128-104 win over Hawks

events.name: LA Clippers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry left midway through the fourth quarter with a left ankle injury as Ivica Zubac and the Los Angeles Clippers spoiled the Golden State Warriors’ home opener with a 112-104 win Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers hold off Warriors as Stephen Curry goes down injured
